description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Staff Nurse Advert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Full and Part time available&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the trauma &amp; orthopedics ward, to work within the existing T&amp;O team. The ideal candidates will be able to work expertly to optimize patient care and must also be a team player who can collaborate and work closely with the existing team to promote excellence in patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a team player who is motivated, enthusiastic and hard- working then we would like to hear from you. In return we can offer excellent opportunities for your personal and professional growth and support your career development in our busy and friendly Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;T&amp;O ward is a 36 bedded ward accommodating trauma patients including spinal injuries. We provide an excellent opportunity to widen skills in a specialist area with on-going education and training for all registered nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following statements are from a newly qualified nurse who started within T&amp;O this year:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Starting my first job as a newly qualified nurse was a daunting prospect but everyone in the team has been so welcoming and supporting. I have really enjoyed working within the team and feel like I have developed diverse skills as a result. I also appreciate the preceptorship days that I have and it has eased my transition between uni and work.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So if you want a new start, there couldn’t be a better time to join us.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisted candidates will be expected to attend an Assessment Centre on one of our sites where you would be required to complete an assessment and attend a formal interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are warmly invited to submit your application once you are in your final year of study at university.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a trained member of staff on the ward you will receive training to become competent in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Induction with a supernumerary period&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An assigned mentor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IV therapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Venepuncture and cannulation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use of PCA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Male catheterisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing ECG’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being a student assessor by attending the mentorship course&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact Matron Amy Read on 01905 763333 and Bleep 521 or ward manager Sue Blackburn on 01905 763333 ext 39554.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
